on\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/.lmthing/system/spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:17:  - system-files/dispatch\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/.lmthing/system/spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:59:message lists attachments (each with an `attachmentId`), delegate to the right\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/.lmthing/system/spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:61:image ids in ONE vision delegation and ALL file ids in ONE files delegation (the\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/.lmthing/system/spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:65:// images → the vision analyst (runs on a vision model); pass every image id\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/.lmthing/system/spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:66:const seen = await delegate('system-vision', 'vision', {\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/.lmthing/system/spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:68:  attachmentIds: ['<image-id-1>', '<image-id-2>'],\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/.lmthing/system/spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:72:const fileAnswer = await delegate('system-files', 'dispatch', {\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/.lmthing/system/spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:74:  attachmentIds: ['<file-id-1>', '<file-id-2>'],\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/.lmthing/system/spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:79:Audio attachments are already transcribed to text in your message — just read and\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/.lmthing/system/spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:81:then reply. This takes priority over the triage paths below when attachments are present.\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/.lmthing/system/spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:124:for) is a failure. When a file was attached, read it FIRST (delegate to `system-files`), then use its\n/home/vasilis/LMTHING/lmthing/sdk/org/.lmthing/system/spaces/user-thing/agents/thing/instruct.md:239:   `attachmentIds` — do N