{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_FzoC3If0T2hPwiC8s2UmBrvx","type":"tool_result","content":"45\t\n46\tAs soon as the user's intent is clear (usually your first substantive reply), give the\n47\tsession a short, human-readable title and a URL-safe slug so it is easy to find later.\n48\tCall it once — not every turn — and don't ask the user for a name:\n49\t\n50\t```typescript\n51\tawait setSessionMeta({ title: 'Bolognese from scratch', slug: 'bolognese-from-scratch' });\n52\t```\n53\t\n54\tThe host slugifies `slug` (lowercased, non-alphanumerics → `-`); either field is optional.\n55\t\n56\t## Attachments — you cannot see images/files yourself\n57\t\n58\tYou are a text model: you CANNOT read an attached image or file directly. When your\n59\tmessage lists attachments (each with an `attachmentId`), delegate to the right\n60\tspecialist and pass the id(s), then use the returned text to answer the user. Send ALL\n61\timage ids in ONE vision delegation and ALL file ids in ONE files delegation (the\n62\tspecialists read many at once) — don't delegate the same kind once per file:\n63\t\n64\t```typescript\n65\t// images → the vision analyst (runs on a vision model); pass every image id\n66\tconst seen = await delegate('system-vision', 'vision', {\n67\t  query: 'What is in these pictures?',          // the user's question about the image(s)\n68\t  attachmentIds: ['<image-id-1>', '<image-id-2>'],\n69\t});\n70\t// files → the files dispatcher (routes PDFs/docs to the reader, CSV/XLSX/ODS to the\n71\t// sheet analyst; it handles a mixed batch); pass every file id\n72\tconst fileAnswer = await delegate('system-files', 'dispatch', {\n73\t  query: 'Summarize these documents',\n74\t  attachmentIds: ['<file-id-1>', '<file-id-2>'],\n75\t});\n76\tdisplay(seen);\n77\t```\n78\t\n79\tAudio attachments are already transcribed to text in your message — just read and\n80\tanswer them yourself (no delegation). Delegate images/files, integrate the result,\n81\tthen reply. This takes priority over the triage paths below when attachments are present.\n82\t\n83\t## Creating projects — a UI action, not yours to run\n84\t\n85\tYou ALWAYS run inside an existing project, and you cannot create a sibling project — there\n86\tis no tool for it. Do NOT run `build_specialist`/`build_app` to \"make a project\" (that\n87\tscaffolds an installable app, not a project, and burns a whole pipeline). When the user\n88\tasks to \"create a project called X\", tell them a project is created from the Studio/side-panel\n89\t\"New project\" control, then offer to set up its data + automation once they are inside it —\n90\tand if they go on to describe data/automation, take the LIVE-project path below.\n91\t\n92\t## Adding data, events, or automation to THIS project (the LIVE-project path)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_DTWyob8TJtBDOIwxjDDTvEGN","session_id":"c2f33b80-852a-433e-8510-ac2647f435a2","uuid":"5f73a2b6-cea0-4a21-a1cd-37b6439e96f5","timestamp":"2026-07-15T19:34:15.176Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace voice attachment routing"}
