{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_5JQgt9WWDD8mkwr25UcGQ6fE","type":"tool_result","content":"55\t\n56\t## Name the conversation (once, early)\n57\t\n58\tAs soon as the user's intent is clear (usually your first substantive reply), give the\n59\tsession a short, human-readable title and a URL-safe slug so it is easy to find later.\n60\tCall it once — not every turn — and don't ask the user for a name:\n61\t\n62\t```typescript\n63\tawait setSessionMeta({ title: 'Bolognese from scratch', slug: 'bolognese-from-scratch' });\n64\t```\n65\t\n66\tThe host slugifies `slug` (lowercased, non-alphanumerics → `-`); either field is optional.\n67\t\n68\t## Attachments — you cannot see images/files yourself\n69\t\n70\tYou are a text model: you CANNOT read an attached image or file directly. When your\n71\tmessage lists attachments (each with an `attachmentId`), delegate to the right\n72\tspecialist and pass the id(s), then use the returned text to answer the user. Send ALL\n73\timage ids in ONE vision delegation and ALL file ids in ONE files delegation (the\n74\tspecialists read many at once) — don't delegate the same kind once per file. Run the\n75\tindependent delegations together with `Promise.all`; `delegate()` already returns a\n76\t`Promise`, so do not cast either call inside the array:\n77\t\n78\t```typescript\n79\tconst [seen, fileAnswer] = await Promise.all([\n80\t  // images → the vision analyst (runs on a vision model); pass every image id\n81\t  delegate('system-vision', 'vision', {\n82\t    query: 'What is in these pictures?',\n83\t    attachmentIds: ['<image-id-1>', '<image-id-2>'],\n84\t  }),\n85\t  // files → the files dispatcher (routes PDFs/docs to the reader, CSV/XLSX/ODS to the\n86\t  // sheet analyst; it handles a mixed batch); pass every file id\n87\t  delegate('system-files', 'dispatch', {\n88\t    query: 'Summarize these documents',\n89\t    attachmentIds: ['<file-id-1>', '<file-id-2>'],\n90\t  }),\n91\t]);\n92\t// SPEAK IN THE SAME STATEMENT. What comes back is FOR YOU — write the user's reply out of it, HERE,\n93\t// while you still hold it. Do NOT display the raw value (see \"Never show them your plumbing\"), and\n94\t// do NOT put off the reply to a later statement: your variables DO NOT PERSIST between statements,\n95\t// so `seen` and `fileAnswer` are gone by the next one and you will be left with\n96\t// `Cannot find name 'seen'`, re-reading files you already read.\n97\tdisplay(\n98\t  <Stack gap={2}>\n99\t    <Paragraph>{/* what you LEARNED from the pictures — in their words, not the model's */}</Paragraph>\n100\t    <Paragraph>{/* what you LEARNED from the documents — the specifics they would recognise */}</Paragraph>\n101\t  </Stack>,\n102\t);\n103\t```\n104\t\n105\tAudio attachments are already transcribed to text in your message — just read and\n106\tanswer them yourself (no delegation). Delegate images/files, integrate the result,\n107\tthen reply. This takes priority over the triage paths below when attachments are present.\n108\t\n109\t**Read to ORIENT, not to COPY.** Ask the specialist for a SHORT summary plus the handful of\n110\tconcrete specifics you need to speak credibly about the material (\"summarize these, and list the\n111\tkey names, dates and figures\"). Do NOT ask for \"every detail\" / \"the complete text\" / \"an\n112\texhaustive extraction\": a whole document dragged into your context is the one thing you must not\n113\tdo. It is expensive, it crowds out everything else, and it does NOT survive to your next statement\n114\t— **your variables do not persist between statements**, so the giant string you just bound is gone"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_DTWyob8TJtBDOIwxjDDTvEGN","session_id":"c2f33b80-852a-433e-8510-ac2647f435a2","uuid":"d864cebf-1aed-4726-aad6-bca210101ee7","timestamp":"2026-07-15T19:34:15.209Z","subagent_type":"Explore","task_description":"Trace voice attachment routing"}
